&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;New Leaf Energy is an experienced clean energy developer that partners with landowners, policymakers, and other stakeholders to accelerate the transition to a world powered by renewable energy. We identify high-value sites, work with landowners and local communities to develop them, and partner with long-term asset owners to bring the most impactful clean energy projects to life.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;New Leaf Energy (NLE) is a national leader in clean energy project development, with a long and successful history first as Borrego Energy’s project development division and then as a stand-alone company.&amp;nbsp; ECP, a leading energy transition focused private equity firm, bought Borrego’s development business in 2022 and founded NLE.&amp;nbsp; Since that time, the company’s product-market mix has grown and diversified, its capital needs have proliferated, and it has become more complex, financially and otherwise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is in this dynamic context that NLE seeks to hire a Senior Vice President, Finance and Capital (SVP). Reporting to the Chief Executive Officer, the SVP will carry responsibility for all the company’s finance and accounting needs, shaping the company’s financial strategy and execution and keeping the company flexible, dynamic, and growing.&amp;nbsp; The SVP will lead NLE’s financial operations, capital markets engagement, and financial planning and analysis.&amp;nbsp; They will partner closely with teams across the company to evaluate new business opportunities, support strategic decision-making, and build the financial infrastructure needed for the company to grow in service of its mission and financial performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate brings deep renewable energy finance experience, strong business judgment, and the ability to balance strategic vision with operational execution in a fast-paced, entrepreneurial environment.&amp;nbsp; Most importantly, our new SVP should be a paragon of the company’s three cultural pillars: transparency, respect, and humility.&amp;nbsp; This position is CFO-track; at the moment we believe SVP is the appropriate level, but you can be promoted to CFO with great performance and company growth that warrants executive team expansion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position responsibilities will include, but are not limited to:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Strategic Leadership&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the CEO, Executive Team, and Board to shape and execute NLE’s strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally to evaluate business opportunities and market strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide financial insight and decision support for investments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help the organization remain agile and financially disciplined amid evolving market conditions, policy changes, and industry disruption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Team Leadership&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, mentor, and develop a high-performing team, fostering a culture of accountability, collaboration, continuous improvement, and business partnership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee accounting, FP&amp;amp;A, treasury, tax, payroll, audit, and financial reporting functions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive process improvements and systems enhancements that increase efficiency, transparency, and analytical capability across Finance and Accounting operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure accurate and timely financial reporting, budgeting, forecasting, and cash flow management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive boundaryless improvements in financial literacy and the ways it can be used to aid operational decision-making across the business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain strong internal controls, financial policies, and governance practices that support a growing and increasingly complex organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt

